Input.question2: For how many days is Diwali celebrated?
Input.question3: What is 2 days before Govardhan Puja?
Answer.Res1: Dhanteras/Yama Deepam and Govardhan Puja/Balipratipada/Gujarati New Year are the names for 2 of the 5 celebration days for the Indian ritual called Diwali. Dhanteras/Yama Deepam is celebrated on October 21, and Govardhan Puja/Balipratipada/Gujarati New Year is celebrated on October 24.  Therefore, Govardhan Puja/Balipratipada/Gujarati New Year is 3 days after Dhanteras/Yama Deepam.
Answer.Res2: Diwali is a religious Indian holiday that lasts for 5 days. It begins on October 21, and lasts until October 25.  Therefore, Diwali is celebrated for 5 days.
Answer.Res3: Each day of the 5-day Indian holiday of Diwali has its own name and events. Naraka Chaturdashi/Kali Chaudas/Hanuman Puja/Chhoti Diwali) happens on October 22, and Govardhan Puja happens on October 24.  Therefore, Naraka Chaturdashi/Kali Chaudas/Hanuman Puja/Chhoti Diwali is  2 days before Govardhan Puja.
